title: CAK remains perfect turning back Clinton at home
text:
CAK remains perfect turning back Clinton at home Updated: Fri 12:25 AM, Oct 09, 2015 / Headlines List / Article 
KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (WVLT) -- Vols head coach Butch Jones was at Christian Academy to watch Warriors tight end and UT commit Austin Pope in action. The senior wouldn't disappoint with a touchdown grab on offense and some terrific plays on defense. 
Quarterback Cole Smith was sharp once again, connecting with Phillip Nichols on a pair of long touchdown passes. Smith was also able to do some damage with his legs finding the promised land by running the football. 
CAK pulls away from Tyler Thackerson and the dragons by a final score of 42-21. The Warriors improve to an impressive 8-0, while Clinton falls to 3-5 on the season.
